Summary: This sub-phase investigates whether Engram-style passive capture or close-session helpers belong in Public at all, and if so, whether they can exist only as thin wrappers over the current JSON-primary save workflow. It defines the research question, baseline measurements, and authority checks needed before any adopt/prototype/reject decision. It does not ship a new save surface.
